# E2E Testing Patterns (Playwright)

## Test Suite Overview

Tests are split into two tiers based on whether they require a live server.

### Tier 1 — Mocked, CI-safe (no server needed)

| File | Covers |
|------|--------|
| `dashboard-pages.spec.ts` | All dashboard tabs, navbar, settings, career tools, sub-tabs |
| `landing.spec.ts` | All landing sections, navbar, CTAs, footer, a11y, cookie consent |
| `auth-pages.spec.ts` | Login/register/forgot/reset/verify form structure + validation |
| `interview-prep.spec.ts` | All states, 4 question sub-tabs, generate/complete/mobile |
| `profile-setup.spec.ts` | Profile setup (resume + 5 steps: basic → work → education → skills → prefs), field validation, navigation |
| `application-detail.spec.ts` | 7 tabs, sub-tabs, cover letter, company, mobile layout |
| `onboarding.spec.ts` | Auto-show/suppress, step nav, skip, complete, `window.Onboarding` API, a11y |
| `complete-coverage.spec.ts` | Authenticated page coverage: dashboard, settings, career tools, history |
| `security.spec.ts` | XSS, JWT format, API headers, content security (all mocked) |
| `extension.spec.ts` | Manifest V3, content script, service worker, popup JS |
| `error-handling.spec.ts` | 401/403/429/500 + mocked network errors, form validation |
| `smoke.spec.ts` | Critical path in ~3 min — use as first CI gate |
| `workflow-mocked.spec.ts` | Workflow processing/complete/error states (mocked) |
| `api-validation.spec.ts` | API response shapes: full/partial/null fields, error bodies, auth tokens |
| `form-edge-cases.spec.ts` | Unicode, boundary values, special characters, XSS |
| `auth-complete.spec.ts` | Google OAuth (mocked), email verification, account lockout |
| `dashboard.spec.ts` | Dashboard nav, mocked settings, tools, history navigation |
| `journey.spec.ts` | Multi-step user journeys: new app → results, career tools flow, auth redirect |
| `keyboard-nav.spec.ts` | Tab/Enter/Space/Escape/Backspace/ArrowDown across all pages |
| `visual-regression.spec.ts` | Page structure verification at desktop/tablet/mobile viewports |
| `performance.spec.ts` | Page load assertions (mocked) |
| `accessibility.spec.ts` | ARIA, landmarks, heading hierarchy |
| `rate-limit.spec.ts` | 429 + Retry-After handling: login, registration, career tools, workflow |
| `file-upload.spec.ts` | Resume/job upload, fixture files, API mock responses, error handling |
| `websocket.spec.ts` | Workflow processing/failed states, progress polling, network resilience |

### Tier 2 — Live server required

These register real users, call real endpoints, and may invoke real LLM agents.
**Do not run in CI without a running server and credentials.**

| File | Needs |
|------|-------|
| `auth.spec.ts` | Real register/login → real DB writes |
| `tools.spec.ts` | Career tool form submissions (requires real session) |
| `workflow.spec.ts` | Full workflow: submit job → poll → results |
| `profile.spec.ts` | Profile CRUD + API key management |

## Running Tests

```bash
cd e2e
npm install && npx playwright install chromium

# CI — all Tier 1 mocked tests (no server needed)
npx playwright test \
  landing auth-pages auth-complete dashboard dashboard-pages \
  profile-setup application-detail interview-prep onboarding \
  workflow-mocked smoke security error-handling complete-coverage \
  visual-regression extension api-validation keyboard-nav rate-limit \
  journey form-edge-cases performance accessibility websocket file-upload \
  --project=chromium --workers=4

# Smoke tests only (~3 min)
SMOKE=1 npx playwright test --project=chromium

# Single suite
npx playwright test tests/onboarding.spec.ts --project=chromium

# Filter by section (A–P letter prefix system)
npx playwright test tests/interview-prep.spec.ts --grep "L\. Content Validation"
npx playwright test tests/onboarding.spec.ts --grep "H\. window\.Onboarding"

# Live-server tests (requires backend running)
uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 &
npx playwright test tests/auth.spec.ts tests/tools.spec.ts --project=chromium
```

## Standard Auth + Cookie Setup (use in every mocked test)

Import from `../utils/api-mocks` — never recreate locally:

```typescript
import { setupAuth, setupAllMocks, MOCK_JWT } from '../utils/api-mocks';

// Inject auth + cookie consent into localStorage before page.goto()
await setupAuth(page);

// Also mock profile + applications API endpoints
await setupAllMocks(page);
```

**CRITICAL**: `MOCK_JWT` is a valid 3-part JWT (`header.payload.sig`). Many client scripts check `token.split('.').length === 3` and redirect to `/auth/login` on failure. Never use a bare string.

**CRITICAL**: Cookie consent MUST include `version: '1.0'`. The banner overlays the page and blocks all pointer events if missing.

## Route Type Annotations — Always Use `(route: any)`

TypeScript `strict: true` requires explicit types on route callbacks:

```typescript
// ✅ Correct — always annotate route as any
await page.route('**/api/v1/profile', (route: any) => route.fulfill({
  status: 200, contentType: 'application/json',
  body: JSON.stringify({ name: 'Test User' }),
}));

// ❌ Breaks TypeScript compilation (implicit any)
await page.route('**/api/v1/profile', route => route.fulfill({ ... }));
```

## API Mocking — beforeEach Pattern

Register routes with `page.route()` **before** `page.goto()`:

```typescript
test.describe('C. Main Content', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
    await setupAuth(page);        // addInitScript first
    await mockExistingData(page); // then route stubs
  });

  test('header renders job title', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto(PAGE_URL);
    await waitForMainContent(page);
    await expect(page.locator('#jobTitle')).toContainText('Engineer');
  });
});
```

Route patterns use `**` prefix to match any origin:
```typescript
await page.route(`**/api/v1/workflow/results/${SESSION_ID}`, (route: any) =>
  route.fulfill({ status: 200, contentType: 'application/json',
    body: JSON.stringify(MOCK_RESULTS) })
);
```

## Data Shape Pitfalls — Arrays vs Strings

Client render functions call `.map()` on API fields. Providing a string where an array is expected throws `s.map is not a function` inside `try/catch`, calling `showError()` and hiding content permanently.

```typescript
// ❌ Breaks renderLogistics()
logistics: { what_to_bring: 'Resume' }

// ✅ Correct
logistics: { what_to_bring: ['Resume'] }
```

**Rule**: These fields MUST be arrays in mock data:
`what_to_bring`, `pre_interview_checklist`, `confidence_boosters`,
`virtual_interview_tips`, `three_key_selling_points`, `required_skills`,
`nice_to_have_skills`, `bullet_points`, `strengths`, `gaps`, `recent_news`

## Waiting for Dynamic Content (SPA State Machines)

Pages with loading → content state transitions need explicit waits:

```typescript
async function waitForMainContent(page: any) {
  await page.locator('#mainContent').waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 10000 });
}
```

**Do NOT** assert visibility immediately after `page.goto()` for data-fetching pages. Always call `waitForMainContent(page)` first.

## Onboarding Tests — window.Onboarding API

`onboarding.js` exposes `window.Onboarding` globally. Key DOM IDs/selectors:

| Element | Selector |
|---------|----------|
| Overlay | `#onboarding-overlay` |
| Modal | `#onboarding-modal` |
| Title | `#onboarding-title` |
| Body | `#onboarding-body` |
| Progress dots | `#onboarding-progress .progress-dot` |
| Next button | `[data-action="onboarding-next"]` |
| Back button | `[data-action="onboarding-prev"]` |
| Skip button | `[data-action="onboarding-skip"]` |

```typescript
// Programmatic control via JS
await page.evaluate(() => (window as any).Onboarding.start());
await page.evaluate(() => (window as any).Onboarding.next());
await page.evaluate(() => (window as any).Onboarding.skip());
await page.evaluate(async () => await (window as any).Onboarding.reset());
```

The tour auto-shows when `localStorage.onboarding_completed` is absent on `/dashboard`.
Suppress it in non-onboarding tests by setting the key in `addInitScript`:

```typescript
localStorage.setItem('onboarding_completed', JSON.stringify({ version: '2.0', completedAt: new Date().toISOString() }));
```

The `api-key` step is conditionally shown — mock `/api/v1/profile/api-key/status` to control it:

```typescript
// Show api-key step
await page.route('**/api/v1/profile/api-key/status', (route: any) => route.fulfill({
  status: 200, body: JSON.stringify({ has_user_key: false, server_has_key: false }),
}));

// Hide api-key step
await page.route('**/api/v1/profile/api-key/status', (route: any) => route.fulfill({
  status: 200, body: JSON.stringify({ has_user_key: true, server_has_key: false }),
}));
```

## Journey Tests — Multi-Step Flow Pattern

`journey.spec.ts` covers realistic user flows. Structure each journey as:

```typescript
test.describe('Journey N — Feature Name', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
    await setupAuth(page);
    // Mock ALL APIs the page touches — don't rely on setupAllMocks alone
    await page.route('**/api/v1/specific-endpoint', (route: any) => route.fulfill({...}));
  });

  test('step 1 — page loads and shows form', async ({ page }) => { ... });
  test('step 2 — can fill and submit form', async ({ page }) => { ... });
  test('step 3 — API is called on submit', async ({ page }) => { ... });
  test('step 4 — result is rendered', async ({ page }) => { ... });
});
```

## Rate Limit Tests — 429 Pattern

Always include `Retry-After` header and an `error_code` in the body:

```typescript
await page.route('**/api/v1/auth/login', (route: any) => route.fulfill({
  status: 429,
  contentType: 'application/json',
  headers: { 'Retry-After': '60' },
  body: JSON.stringify({ detail: 'Too many requests', error_code: 'RATE_4001' }),
}));
```

Every 429 test MUST verify:
1. `errors.length === 0` (no JS errors)
2. Page remains visible
3. User stays on the same page (not redirected)

## SPA Redirect Chains — Flexible Access Control Tests

A 401 from the API causes JS to do `window.location.href = '/auth/login'`. If a valid token exists in localStorage, the login page immediately bounces back to `/dashboard`. Don't assert a fixed final URL — assert that the page navigated *away* from the protected page:

```typescript
// ❌ Breaks when login → dashboard redirect chain fires
await page.waitForURL(/auth\/login/, { timeout: 8000 });

// ✅ Robust
await page.waitForTimeout(2000);
const stillOnProtectedPage = page.url().includes('/application/');
expect(stillOnProtectedPage).toBe(false);
```

## Keyboard Navigation Tests

All keyboard assertions use `page.evaluate()` to inspect `document.activeElement`:

```typescript
// Check focused element type
const tag = await page.evaluate(() => document.activeElement?.tagName);
expect(['A', 'BUTTON', 'INPUT'].includes(tag || '')).toBeTruthy();

// Check focused element's data-action
const action = await page.evaluate(() =>
  document.activeElement?.getAttribute('data-action')
);
expect(action).toBe('onboarding-next');
```

For select elements, use `ArrowDown` (not `Alt+Down`) for cross-browser compatibility.

## Multi-Step Form Navigation (Profile Setup)

Steps have client-side required-field validation. Fill required fields before clicking **Next**:

```typescript
async function goToStep2(page: any) {
  await fillStep1Required(page);  // populate required fields first
  await page.route('**/api/v1/profile/basic-info', (route: any) =>
    route.fulfill({ status: 200, contentType: 'application/json', body: '{"success":true}' })
  );
  await page.locator('#nextBtn').click();
  await page.locator('#step2').waitFor({ state: 'visible' });
}
```

## waitForURL for Redirect Tests

`window.location.href` redirects can abort the frame. Use `Promise.all` with a silent catch:

```typescript
await Promise.all([
  page.waitForURL(/dashboard/, { timeout: 8000 }).catch(() => {}),
  page.locator('#loginBtn').click(),
]);
```

## Locator Safety — Avoid `isAttached()`

`Locator.isAttached()` is not available in Playwright 1.40. Use `count() > 0` instead:

```typescript
// ❌ TS2339: Property 'isAttached' does not exist on type 'Locator'
if (await select.isAttached()) { ... }

// ✅ Correct
if (await select.count() > 0) { ... }
```

## Test Section Organisation (A–P lettered describes)

Large page suites use single-letter prefixes so `--grep` can isolate sections:

```
A. Page Structure & Loading State
B. Generate State / Error State
C. First Step Content (e.g. welcome)
D–G. Navigation (Next, Back, Skip, Complete)
H. Global API (window.Onboarding, window.app)
I. Conditional Logic
J–L. Content Validation, Mobile Layout, Additional Structure
M–P. Extended scenarios
```

## Common Issues

| Issue | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| `mainContent` never visible | Check render functions for `.map()` on a non-array mock field |
| Cookie banner blocks clicks | Add `cookie_consent` with `version:'1.0'` in `addInitScript` |
| Page redirects to `/dashboard` during access control test | Assert URL moved *away* from protected path, not to a specific destination |
| `browserType.launch: Executable doesn't exist` | Run `npx playwright install chromium` (must use `required_permissions: ["all"]` in Cursor sandbox) |
| Multi-step wizard won't advance past step N | Fill all required fields for step N before clicking Next |
| `token.split('.').length !== 3` bounces to login | Use `MOCK_JWT` from `../utils/api-mocks` — it is a real 3-part JWT |
| Profile setup redirects to dashboard | Mock `/api/v1/profile/**` to return incomplete profile data |
| `waitForURL` throws `net::ERR_ABORTED` | Wrap in `Promise.all([waitForURL(...).catch(()=>{}),...])` |
| TS7006 `route` implicit any | Always write `(route: any) => route.fulfill(...)` |
| `isAttached` TS error | Replace with `count() > 0` check |
| Onboarding blocks test interactions | Set `onboarding_completed` in `addInitScript` to suppress the tour |
